</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garielhalliwell>Gariel Halliwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1146<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 9:07:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25464.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stats for a new Wiz</span><hr size=1> Put all you can into Intelligence, then stick your other five points in Strength, Stamina or Agility depending on which school of thought you follow.<br>
<br>
Sage Gariel Halliwell<br>
Arcanist of The Hand, Xev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jear@graffeswizardcompilation>Jear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 9:13:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25464.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sta</span><hr size=1> Well with pop HP is way way way more important then Agi. Sta is the way to go. HP is what makes you live your AC will, unless you go 100% after it, be too low to realy make that big a differance. <br>
Str well umm a waste of time atm with full gear on and stuff I usualy don't weigh more then 40 and with 103 in str I can have alot of items before I am encoumbered and aye there are alot of WR bags out there fairly easy to get your hands on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So I would if I where you choose int all you can get then sta. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 6548<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 9:27:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25464.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sta</span><hr size=1> What race are you playing?  Anything except Human and Frog I would say put half the points into INT and the rest into STA.  INT isn't that important of a stat anymore because there are SO many INT items out there now.  It's still important, don't get me wrong, but it's easier to raise INT than it is STA. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Officer of Triton, Member of Team Ice, Povar<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=458434">Rombus, Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5702">Rommy, 61 High Priest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=obiquon1>Obiquon1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Member of Team Xuzl</span><br>  Posts: 1931<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 9:31:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25464.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/beaune414/obisml.txt WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sta</span><hr size=1> are you twinking the hell out of your wiz? If so, STA might be a nice option for the extra HP. However, if youre saving rat wiskers... go with some extra INT. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=562718&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/beaune414/obiquon4.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skewert>Skewert</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 9:39:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25464.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sta</span><hr size=1> I'd say put 25 into int, and the extra 5 into Str.  As I understand it, if you put the extra 5 into stamina, that will only equal a little over 10hp's, and not untill lvl 60.  At lvl 60, and especially in the PoP zones, 10 hp's is nothing...... 5 str will help you carry a little more loot, and will help balance out the neg 8 str if you make the wise choice to go Solusek Ro, and then get the rings as well.<br>
<br>
Just to clarify, unless I'm mistaken, Necro's get less than 2.5 hp's per point of stamina at lvl 60, and I think Wizards are on the same table.  So those extra 5 Stamina points at creation, will only equal like 12-13 hp's at lvl 60.  As a physically weak wizard, you'll certainly become encumbered somewhere during your journey, and the extra 5 str will come in handy much more than 12-13 hp's at lvl 60 IMO. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skewert>Skewert</A> at: 3/20/03 9:43:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fazzaryaayrazzaf>Fazzarya Ayrazzaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 5:35:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25464.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sta</span><hr size=1> Depends on what your end game goals are. If you *think your going to go to at least level 60 then I recommend 20 stam 10 int. If you are going to just screw around with him, then go all int for the mana and the rest into strength. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223084&amp;amp;resize=true" target="&quot;top&quot;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Fazzarya Ayrazzaf</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arcanist<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.solinvictus.org/eq/">Sol Invictus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 12077<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 6:15:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25464.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-side-02.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stats for a new Wiz</span><hr size=1> Click the link, the lovely candy-colored link:<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.arcanist.com/modules.php?name=Reviews&rop=showcontent&id=11">www.arcanist.com/modules....tent&id=11</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz_toon.gif" height="104" width="390" alt="stats" border=0></a>
